<subSubSection id="FB634C8DD16DDAAB3D1DB08C582B4988" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="ED67FF0C1374B17A634B7C31D2FD3DC5" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EE2CF910BB7936CAB0966277B9316BD6" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">
In Macau, adults are active only in the spring and range in total length 9.5-15 mm and 2-4 mm in maximum width. Although they have been found mainly around artificial lights at night, they have also been observed feeding on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="F06B6FA2CD4CE0BA596E4BC1350A9F94" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Caprifoliaceae" genus="Lonicera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lonicera japonica" order="Dipsacales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="japonica">
<emphasis id="2D9FFEC87A6E4E0F06AE1416769C0101" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Lonicera japonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2E474AD5F5402F052DF2E4246C3DCDD8" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rubiaceae" genus="Gardenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Gardenia jasminoides" order="Gentianales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="jasminoides">
<emphasis id="F9217A799A26C16A44627F8A7EE86AF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Gardenia jasminoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
during daytime (RP &amp; LC pers. obs.). Larval host plants include 
<taxonomicName id="07BD75F0635E68E31CFD6F03B546DF83" genus="Artidesma" lsidName="Artidesma tetrandrum" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" rank="species" species="tetrandrum">
<emphasis id="23DC74F26E782F1B5231748FABFAD92B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Artidesma tetrandrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="7F79C541D339D25842A532760EFB9A30" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bauhinia malabarica" order="Rosales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="malabarica">
<emphasis id="47EB6B85D8536266CB804160E76BD425" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Bauhinia malabarica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="E75FCB8A2E88BD1577353BF2344C807C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lecythidaceae" genus="Careya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Careya arborea" order="Polemoniales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="arborea">
<emphasis id="7A38ACC48948F183A9337DB8F1E579CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Careya arborea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="90DC98E912C5FA70729EE3CB9A0229A5" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Sterculiaceae" genus="Heritiera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Heritiera minor" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="minor">
<emphasis id="CA890C293EE9925870E10F18B2A223C9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Heritiera minor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="0E3C36C1CFCDD25D90E8DDC675826E1E" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Lythraceae" genus="Lagerstroemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Lagerstroemia parviflora" order="Myrtiflorae" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="parviflora">
<emphasis id="3492B2C157305436E5041A166FF042DE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Lagerstroemia parviflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="84F560A65F87FF68B7A8569C4C8EE92E" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Dipterocarpaceae" genus="Shorea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Shorea robusta" order="Guttiferales" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="robusta">
<emphasis id="820B8CD83DDC3E8DB62D60A270B1EF40" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="79">Shorea robusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="9DBDD4A032D5D4ABB5338D5586E1ADF2" author="Duffy, EAJ" journalOrPublisher="British Museum, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="79" refId="B34" refString="Duffy, EAJ, 1968. A monograph of the immature stages of Oriental timber beetles (Cerambycidae). British Museum (Natural History), London, [viii +] 434 pp. [198 figs, 18 pls]" title="A monograph of the immature stages of Oriental timber beetles (Cerambycidae). British Museum (Natural History), London, [viii +] 434 pp. [198 figs, 18 pls]" year="1968">Duffy 1968</bibRefCitation>
